  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: be734eb0a3f16d045a718d19c4fcbf20, type: 3}
  m_Name: NPCDialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCDialogue
  npcName: Peacock
  npcPortrait: {fileID: -9178916439338732956, guid: 9ec5b92b9137d00449c293ab58b68f5c, type: 3}
  dialogueLines:
  - (A beautiful peacock stands before me. I would like to ask him more about this
    strange  garden I have found myself in, but...)
  - (...Something seems to be troubling him. Perhaps I could help?)
  - What splendor in your stride! Yet it seems a shield against unseen wounds.
  - Peacock, why such fierce display in this lonely corner of the garden?
  - "Your intrusion is unwanted. My plumage is unmatched, yet they cast me out for
    Snake\u2019s lies."
  - I am in no mood for your platitudes. Pester someone else!
  - (Peacock seems very sensitive right now. How should I approach this...?)
  - 'You boast unmatched beauty, yet banishment festers. '
  - Does this flamboyance truly heal the wound, or merely mask it? Isolation only
    deepens the shadow.
  - What could a mere wanderer like you know of such matters? You are only a child
    in these affairs.
  - " If you live to grow old, may fate rip your life\u2019s purpose away as it has
    mine\u2014then you might begin to understand."
  - Until then, learn to keep your nose out of the business of your elders!
  - "This \u201Ccelestial wealth\u201D you claim\u2014does it not echo the Painter\u2019s
    gift, yet hide a deeper truth? I have wandered deserts cast out as \u201Cmad,\u201D
    yet love revealed worth beyond appearances."
  - Show me your true feathers; deception only betrays the soul.
  - "You dare expose what I conceal? This\u2026 this lie was my armor!"
  - Your new purpose lies not in borrowed glory, but confronting the deception and
    growing at your own pace.
  - "The snake\u2019s lies thrive in hiding; truth unfolds in time."
  - "Insufferable\u2026"
  - (That did not seem to go over well... Maybe I should try again.)
  - "I see the pain beneath the display. I too have known separation from my Layla\u2014cast
    out, called mad, learning to trust my own pace amid the world\u2019s scorn."
  - Shame need not chain you; true feathers emerge not by force, but by walking the
    path unafraid.
  - "You\u2026 speak as one who has tasted exile. But my paradise of perfection is
    lost forever to the snake. What use is your pity?"
  - "Then let us pursue the truth together. I carry this falsehood as reminder\u2014its
    shine deceives, but your natural light awaits."
  - "You followed\u2026 even with that cursed thing. Why?"
  - "\u201CLife unfolds not in hasty display or borrowed shine,\nBut in the quiet
    pace where the soul aligns."
  - "\"Like Majnun\u2019s love that bloomed through desert trial,\nOr the seeker
    who rejects the drop for the eternal sea\u2014"
  - "\"Trust the feathers nature grants in its own time;\nThe snake\u2019s lies fade
    when the heart walks free."
  - "\"Body or soul\u2014which claims the truer throne?\nBe whole: renounce the seem,
    and claim your own.\u201D"
  - Your words pierce deeper than any thorn. Isolation has only worsened this self-hatred.
  - "Leaning on another\u2026 it is not weakness?"
  - "Never. I learned in exile that true strength is compassion\u2014for others and
    the self I once despised. The hoopoe taught the birds: paradise is but a mote
    in the sun\u2019s true beam."
  - ' Your plumage was never the measure; the journey reveals the Whole.'
  - "Then I will return with you. This feather proves the snake\u2019s deception\u2014his
    lies that turned my pride to poison."
  - I lashed out because I feared my own incompleteness. No more hiding.
  - "You have shown me what the manuscripts whisper: outer splendor is illusion.
    The soul\u2019s pace is its own paradise."
  - Thank you, wanderer. I am no longer banished from myself.
  - '(And so another learns: life is your own, and you move at a pace. Trust yourself.)'
  - '* Poem added to Book'
  autoProgressLines: 
  endDialogueLines: 0000000000000000000000000000000000000100000000000000000000000000000000000001
  autoProgressDelay: 1.5
  typingSpeed: 0.05
